# API Integration Guidelines

## Case Transformation

**Critical:** Backend uses `snake_case`, frontend uses `camelCase`.

All API responses MUST be transformed using [apiTransformers.ts](mdc:src/utils/apiTransformers.ts).

### Automatic Transformation

The shared axios client in [axios.ts](mdc:src/api/lib/axios.ts) automatically handles transformations:

```typescript
// Requests: camelCase → snake_case (automatic)
// Responses: snake_case → camelCase (automatic)

// Just use camelCase in your code:
const patient = await getPatient(1);
console.log(patient.fullName); // ✅ Automatically transformed
```

### Manual Transformation

If you need to transform manually:

```typescript
import { transformKeys } from "@/utils/apiTransformers";

// Response transformation
const frontendData = transformKeys.toCamelCase(backendResponse);

// Request transformation
const backendData = transformKeys.toSnakeCase(frontendData);
```

## API Function Pattern

All API functions follow this structure:

```typescript
// src/api/[resource]/index.ts

import api from "../lib/axios";
import { Patient } from "@/types/types";

// GET - Fetch single item
export async function getPatient(id: number): Promise<Patient> {
  const response = await api.get(`/patients/${id}`);
  return response.data; // Already transformed by interceptor
}

// GET - Fetch list
export async function getPatients(): Promise<Patient[]> {
  const response = await api.get("/patients");
  return response.data;
}

// POST - Create
export async function createPatient(
  data: Omit<Patient, "id">
): Promise<Patient> {
  const response = await api.post("/patients", data);
  return response.data;
}

// PUT/PATCH - Update
export async function updatePatient(
  id: number,
  data: Partial<Patient>
): Promise<Patient> {
  const response = await api.put(`/patients/${id}`, data);
  return response.data;
}

// DELETE
export async function deletePatient(id: number): Promise<void> {
  await api.delete(`/patients/${id}`);
}
```

## React Query Integration

Wrap API functions with React Query:

```typescript
// src/api/query/hooks/usePatientQueries.ts

import { useQuery, useMutation, useQueryClient } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { getPatient, createPatient, updatePatient } from "@/api/patients";

// Query hook
export function usePatient(id: number) {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ["patient", id],
    queryFn: () => getPatient(id),
    enabled: !!id,
  });
}

// Mutation hook
export function useCreatePatient() {
  const queryClient = useQueryClient();

  return useMutation({
    mutationFn: createPatient,
    onSuccess: () => {
      queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ["patients"] });
    },
  });
}
```

## Error Handling

The shared axios client includes error interceptors. Handle errors in components:

```typescript
const { data, isLoading, error } = usePatient(id);

if (error) {
  return <ErrorDisplay message="Failed to load patient" />;
}
```

## Type Safety

### Frontend Types (camelCase)

```typescript
// src/types/types.ts
export interface Patient {
  id: number;
  fullName: string;
  birthDate: string;
  phoneNumber: string;
}
```

### Backend Types (snake_case)

Only needed for reference or custom handling:

```typescript
// Backend response structure
interface PatientResponse {
  id: number;
  full_name: string;
  birth_date: string;
  phone_number: string;
}
```

